, Toni Morrison, Harmony Holiday, and Essex Hemphill. Writerly and experimental, Millennial Style theorizes contemporary black art as the holding (or hoarding) of black mortal and material resources against the injuries of social death, as the fashioning of relational ethics, and as exuberant black world-building in ruinous times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican American artsy21st century. 0aAfrican diaspora in art. 0aAfrican diaspora in literature. 0aAmerican literaturexAfrican American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aPolitics and culturezUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aPsychic trauma. 0aQueer theory. 0aWomanism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / African American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311135689140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478059196?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478059196423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478059196/original  a978-3-11-135689-1  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles